---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What Morristown Eats is, how it works, and why it exists."
>
  <style>
    .about-header {
      padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
      border-bottom: 3px solid var(--color-ink);
    }
    .about-header h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
      color: var(--color-ink);
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .about-lede {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      max-width: 600px;
      font-style: italic;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-rust);
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .about-body {
      max-width: 660px;
      padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
    }
    .about-section {
      padding: 2.5rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-paper-dark);
    }
    .about-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .about-section h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .about-section p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .about-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .rules-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    }
    .rules-list li {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      padding: 0.6rem 0 0.6rem 1.5rem;
      border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--color-paper-dark);
      position: relative;
    }
    .rules-list li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      font-family: var(--font-display);
    }
    .rules-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .ownership-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .ownership-table th {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted);
      text-align: left;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem 0.5rem 0;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-ink);
    }
    .ownership-table td {
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem 0.75rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-paper-dark);
      vertical-align: top;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .ownership-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .tier-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      background: var(--color-paper-dark);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-ink);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .about-author {
      background: var(--color-paper-dark);
      border: 2px solid var(--color-ink);
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--color-ink);
      padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
      margin-top: 3rem;
    }
    .about-author p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .about-author p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .about-author .sig {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      color: var(--color-rust);
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .about-header { padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
      .about-body { padding: 2.5rem 0 4rem; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="about-header">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="label">About this project</span>
      <h1>Morristown Eats</h1>
      <p class="about-lede">
        A personal restaurant guide to Morristown, NJ — built on honest visits,
        independent judgment, and no financial relationships with anyone I cover.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-body">

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Why this exists</h2>
        <p>
          Morristown has genuinely good restaurants. Salvadoran cooking with real range.
          A bagel counter that's been running the same operation since before most residents
          moved here. Greek-Mediterranean that holds its own. Vietnamese breakfast.
          None of this is easy to find.
        </p>
        <p>
          The problem isn't the food — it's the coverage. Yelp is noise: three-star reviews
          from 2019 mixed in with fresh complaints about parking. Google surfaces whoever
          paid for the placement. The local food coverage that does exist is mostly a press
          release rewrite dressed as journalism, cycling the same downtown spots on rotation.
        </p>
        <p>
          Nobody was doing the straightforward thing: visiting restaurants, eating the food,
          paying their own check, and writing down what they actually thought.
          So I started doing that.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>How I work</h2>
        <p>
          Every restaurant in this guide has been either personally visited or flagged
          clearly as unvisited. When I visit, I go as a regular customer. I don't announce
          myself. I pay my own bill.
        </p>
        <p>
          Profiles go up when I've formed a real opinion — not before. Restaurants I've
          confirmed are open and real but haven't eaten at yet appear in the database as
          unvisited and get a full profile only after I've been there.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I write, I'm asking a few simple questions: does this place do what it's
          trying to do? Is there something specific worth ordering? Would I send a friend
          here? A neighborhood diner running the same Saturday breakfast for thirty years
          is more interesting to this guide than a well-funded opening that's been on
          every food Instagram account in the state.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Who appears here</h2>
        <p>The guide covers restaurants in Morristown. Ownership matters — here's the framework:</p>
        <table class="ownership-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Tier</th>
              <th>What it means</th>
              <th>Coverage</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier-label">Independent</span></td>
              <td>Privately owned, no institutional ownership or PE backing</td>
              <td>Full editorial coverage</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier-label">Local group</span></td>
              <td>NJ-focused ownership, 3 or fewer locations</td>
              <td>Full coverage, labeled</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier-label">Regional</span></td>
              <td>Broader footprint, still genuinely good</td>
              <td>Awards categories only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier-label">National chain</span></td>
              <td>Corporate ownership, wide footprint</td>
              <td>Not covered</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
          When ownership is ambiguous, I research it and say what I found.
          The ownership tier is listed on every profile.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>No ratings. No stars.</h2>
        <p>
          I don't publish star ratings or aggregate scores. Numbers flatten context
          and encourage comparison over discovery. A 4.2 doesn't tell you whether
          to order the dumplings. A specific recommendation does.
        </p>
        <p>
          What I publish instead is a judgment — what the place is good at,
          what you should order, and what kind of occasion it's right for.
          That's more useful than a number.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>No pay-to-play. No exceptions.</h2>
        <p>
          No restaurant has paid to be listed, rated, or featured. No restaurant
          has paid for better placement, a faster profile, or favorable coverage.
          This isn't unusual in principle — it's how restaurant journalism is
          supposed to work. It's just not how most local food coverage actually works.
        </p>
        <p>
          I intend to keep it this way indefinitely. If that ever changes, I'll say so clearly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-author">
        <p>
          I live in Morristown with my family. We eat out constantly — probably more
          than we should. I've been eating around this town long enough to know what's
          good, what used to be good, and what's getting better.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is the guide I wanted to exist.
        </p>
        <p class="sig">— Matthew</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
